The paper discusses a new learning paradigm in artificial intelligence, which is a broad area of computer science. The paper specifically focuses on Small Sample Learning (SSL), which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper discusses SSL techniques that can be categorized into two categories: concept learning and experience learning. These categories are related to several subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
